original:
{"Touch":{"0":"An irregularity in the galley: the table is neatly laid, but the plates are glued in place and the cutlery nailed down. The culprit is quickly discovered when she tries to nail the chief engineer's hat to the chief engineer's head. "Everything has its place," she explains when she's dragged before you.","21":"A crewman is staring fixedly from a stained-glass window. "Look!" he points out at the apparently ordinary sky. "Webs, strung between the stars! And watch. Watch! There – did you see the stars shiver? Like dew on the cobweb when the spider stirs?" You saw no such thing.","61":"One of your engineers has taken an oath of utter silence. He refuses to speak, or make any sound at all. He has gagged himself, and wrapped rags around his feet to muffle his footsteps. He refuses to employ either wrench or hammer. He is not, as it stands, much use.","41":"A junior signaller is discovered in the hold amidst a pile of dissected books. She is cutting out words and grouping them in clusters to represent a new system of linguistic categorisation. "Narrative is preposterous and occlusive," she informs you. "Meaning is the only sensible foundation for classification." You examine her arrangements. The words 'light' and 'law' sit side-by-side. Nearby, 'conjunction', 'philosophy' and 'faction'  huddle together.","81":"You discover a stoker angrily defacing the engine's bible. He claims that here in the heavens, there are more pertinent gods than that of King James. Immediately, he launches into a sermon about the Burrower Below: the wyrm-mother, general-progenitrix of the Devourers of Days, who are called the Aeginae. "She tunnelled the paths across the sky! Every transit is a trespass! We must give praise!"","91":"Someone has been making subtle amendments to your Navigator's calculations, presumably in an attempt to alter your course. The culprit is discovered to be a reticent engineer.

You demand an explanation. She once encountered the Storm that Speaks, and it spoke to her in voices that she had thought she'd never hear again. Ever since, she has been trying to find it once more."},"Dream":{"0":"You dream of a storm whose lightning scratches words across the sky, and whose thunder is a cacophony of voices belonging to people you have known. Its winds pluck, pitifully, at your clothes. You are wearing black: sombre, funereal black.","41":"A dream of a midnight meadow. Above you the stars are going out one by one, as if their gas-pipes had been turned off. Flowers bloom in the dark, coloured in a spectrum of blacks that were heretofore imperceptible: the black of grief, the black of before-times, the blacks of liberation and of possibility. A rainbow arches across the newly empty sky, in seven subtle shades. All black, of course.","61":"The sky of your dream is blazing gold. It is peppered – no, crowded – with suns. Suns piled on suns, like the groats in a miser's hoard.

Their light floods you. It shines through skin and blood and meat, picking out your branching veins and the slender pillars of your bones. Is there no more to you than this? ","21":"You dream of falling. It's a common dream, here. The fogs that bedevil the High Wilderness are thick about you, and through them, below, you see something stir. A beast. A behemoth. Almost a dragon; almost a whale; almost a continent. It gnaws on the roots of heaven, and all the fogs of the Wilderness are its steaming breath. Its maw opens, wide as the gulf between stars."},"Discontent":{"51":"An engineer cries out, her voice hoarse as a professional mourner. "It's gone!" She points through one of the stained-glass windows. "A star! It winked out!" You look through the glass. Stars burn upon the firmament. The specific patch of sky she's pointing to is indeed empty, but you couldn't say if a star had been there before.","0":"A junior signaller receives a dose of medicinal port in the infirmary, after seeing a frozen corpse spin past a window. The experience has shaken him. "The dead are hungry!" he says. "We need to make an offerin', or it'll come back, a-knockin' at the hull!""}}

translation:
{"Touch":{"0":"厨房里出现反常现象：桌子摆得整整齐齐，但盘子是用胶水粘的，餐具用钉子钉在上面。当她试图把首席工程师的帽子钉在首席工程师的头上时，这起事件的罪魁祸首就很快被发现了。当她被拖到你面前时，她解释说："一切都有它应在的位置。","21":"一个船员正定定地盯着一扇彩色玻璃窗。"看！"他指着显然是一如往常的天空。"网，串起群星的网！看哪，看那里！你看到星星在颤抖了吗？就像蜘蛛网上的露水被蜘蛛搅动一样？"而你什么也没看见。","61":"你的一个工程师突然发誓要保持完全的沉默。他拒绝说话，也拒绝发出任何动静。他把自己的嘴堵上，在脚上缠上破布来压下脚步声。他拒绝使用扳手或锤子。就目前而言，他不算是一个派得上用场的人。","41":"在货舱里的一堆被解剖过的书中发现了车上的一名初级信号员。她正在剪下单词并将它们分组，以此来表示一种新的语言学分类系统。她告诉你："叙事是自相矛盾而闭塞的。意义是分类的唯一合理的基础"。你检查了一下她的分类。“光”和“法律”这两个词并在一起。在它们附近，“联合”、“哲学”和“派别”挤在一起。","81":"你发现一名司炉在愤怒地涂抹着机车上的圣经。他声称这里的天堂有比詹姆士国王更贴切的神明。随即，他开始了关于下之掘隧神的布道：亚龙之母，被称为天虬的噬日者们的总祖先。"她在天空中开凿了隧道！每一次过境都是一种侵犯！我们必须崇敬她！"","91":"有人一直在对你的导航仪的计算进行细微的修正，想必是在尝试改变你的航线。肇事者是一名沉默寡言的工程师。

你要求她作出解释。她曾经遇到过言语之风暴神，祂用她以为再也听不到的声音对她说话。从那时起，她就一直试图再一次找到祂。"},"Dream":{"0":"你梦见一场风暴，闪电在天空中划出文字，你熟人的声音混杂成雷声。风楚楚可怜地拨弄着你的衣服。你穿着黑色的衣服：阴沉的、葬礼上的黑色。","41":"一个关于午夜草地的梦。在你的上方，星星一个接一个地熄灭，就像它们的煤气管被关掉了一样。花朵在黑暗中绽放，染上了以前无法察觉的黑色光谱：悲痛的黑色，以前的黑色，解放的黑色和可能性的黑色。一道彩虹在新的空旷的天空中拱起，有七个微妙的色调。当然，都是黑色。","61":"你梦中的天野金光四射。它上面洒满了，不，是挤满了太阳。太阳堆在太阳上，就像守财奴囤积的麦粒。

它们的光芒漫过你。光芒闪耀，穿过皮肤、血液和肉，照亮了你的血管和你的细骨柱。你身上就只剩这些东西了吗？","21":"你梦见你在坠落。在这里，经常会有人梦到这个场景。困扰天野的大雾在你四周弥漫。透过它们看去，在下面，你看到有什么东西在翻腾着。兽。巨兽。像一条龙那么大，像一头鲸鱼那么大，像一块大陆那么大。它啃噬着高天的根，天野中一切雾气都是它蒸腾的吐息。它的巨嘴大开，宽如星辰间的沟壑。"},"Discontent":{"51":"一名工程师大喊着，她的声音嘶哑得像一位职业哭灵人。"它不见了！"她指着其中一扇彩色玻璃窗说，"一颗星星！它闭上了眼！"你透过玻璃看去，星星在苍穹上燃烧。她所指的那片区域确实是空荡的，但你无法确定之前是否有一颗星星在那里。","0":"一名初级信号员在看到一具冰冷的尸体从窗前旋过后去医务室打了一针。这次经历让他的精神动摇了。"死者很饿！"他说。"我们要献上贡品,  否则它们就会回来，把我们抓走！""}}

original:
{"CircusPortDescription":{"1":"And visitors seem to agree! Cheery calliope music thunders from the Big Top and through the many, polished amusement stands. 

Such is the lure of the renewed carnival, that people are coming from as far as London itself to partake. Many of them never leave. A small shanty-town has been established just outside of the tents where they sit and laugh and plan to return home – just not today. Tomorrow, perhaps. After one more performance.","0":"The reality is not impressive. Aside from the big-top that dominates the Circus, the place is shabby: poorly maintained, and even more poorly attended. 

Bored-looking circus folk run rotting booths. The clowns' painted-on smiles are no match for the deep-set misery behind the greasepaint. Even the calliope music, playing on a run-down piano, is more 'grimly resolute' than cheery."}}

translation:
{"CircusPortDescription":{"1":"而游客们看起来也同意这一点！欢快的蒸汽笛风琴音乐从大帐篷上响起，穿过无数抛光过的游乐摊位。

新举办的狂欢节引人入胜，吸引着来自遥远伦敦的人们。他们中的许多人从未离开。帐篷外建了一个小小的棚户城镇，他们在那里坐着，笑着，打算回家——但不是今天。或许等明天再回去。等到再看完一场演出也不迟。","0":"但现状可没那么吸引人。除了主宰马戏团的大帐篷之外，这个地方很破旧：维护不善，参观的人更是寥寥无几。

百无聊赖的马戏团员工经营着破败的摊位。小丑们脸上涂抹的笑脸与油彩背后深藏的苦闷相形见绌。甚至用那台破琴演奏的蒸汽笛风琴音乐，也显得“严肃而坚定”，而非愉快。}}

original:
{"Barrows":{"0":"Barrows","30":"The sigils, scored into the barrow's earth, smoulder. The incandescent language is searing.  A command burns your marrow: 'HERE, YOU WILL BE SILENT.'","35":"The entrances to the barrows have been filled with piles of rock; they are stoppered with slate and shale. Beneath your feet, the Correspondence is incandescent: 'WE HAVE RAISED YOU UP AND SO SHALL WE CAST YOU DOWN.'"},"Grave":{"80":"The Grave is quiet now.","100":"A forlorn moan emanates from deep within. The Gate is locked for always.","110":"The Grave is empty and silent as death. Whatever once dwelt here does no longer.","0":"
Here, at the heart of the forest, a great barrow built from ancient stone stands. Gates of star-forged bronze block the entrance.	","60":"At the foot of the stair is a burial chamber, fathoms high. Hanging from the roof is a skeleton. The bones are the size of locomotives; the skull palatial. Red Correspondence sigils are branded on the bones. The trisected skull's mouth is sealed shut with chorister wax.","70":"The scholar translates. "The servant was given a task, They mean to complete it. But they have no body. They mean to chain the wood. No— tame it. They are the Tamer. They overstepped when they gave voice to the voiceless. They want to undo their error." The scholar falls silent. "Sorry. What?" Their eyes widen. "They want one of us to help them. For a year and a day.""},"Giggling":{"0":"You inch forward as the laughter crescendos, washing over you. A copse of trees, grey as a rainstorm, lies ahead. It blocks the rest of the dell from sight. But it is the only way forward.","16":"A canopy of dripping leaves conceals what lies ahead. Laughter, high and mirthless, can be heard very close by. You must go forward."},"Summerset":{"100":"The camp is deserted. The scholars have left the wood: there is nothing left for them here. The banners of Summerset flap forlornly in the wind.","0":"A cluster of scholars has set up camp on the border of the wood. Their funding gone, they struggle to continue their research into whoever is entombed in the Regent's Grave.

The wind howls in the trees, and the skies threaten rain. The scholars huddle in their tents, brooding over papers and conspiring against colleagues."}}

translation:
{"Barrows":{"0":"Barrows","30":"刻在荒冢地上的符印在微光中闷燃。这炽亮的语言灼烧着眼睛。一道命令在你骨髓中燃烧：“此地，汝须沉默。”","35":"荒冢的入口已被成堆岩石堵死——石板与页岩将其封口。你脚下的信符炽亮如火：“我们曾将你高举，如今亦将令你坠落。”"},"Grave":{"80":"墓穴如今已归于寂静。","100":"一声孤寂的呻吟从深处传来。大门已永远封锁。","110":"墓穴空无一物，静寂如死。曾居于此者已不复存在。","0":"
此处，在森林的心脏地带，一座由远古石块筑成的巨冢巍然矗立。星铸青铜打造的巨门封锁着入口。	","60":"阶梯底端是一座高达数丈的墓室。天花板上悬挂着一具骸骨——骨如火车车厢般巨大，头骨如宫殿般宏伟。红色的信符符印烙于骨上。那具分裂为三面的头骨，其口已被唱诗蜂蜡封死。","70":"学者翻译道："这仆从曾被赋予使命。它意图完成这使命，但它没有身体。它想将这片林地束缚——不，是驯服。它是驯师。它赋予无声者声音，以至于僭越。如今它想纠正错误。"学者顿了一下，"抱歉，什么？"他瞪大眼睛，"它想让我们之中的一人协助它。持续一年零一天。""},"Giggling":{"0":"你缓缓前行，笑声愈加响亮，如浪潮般袭来。前方，一片如暴雨般暗淡的树林遮蔽了山谷的他处。但你只能往前走。","16":"一片滴着水的树冠遮蔽了前路。高亢而空洞的笑声就在近旁。你必须前行。"},"Summerset":{"100":"营地已被废弃。学者们已离开这片林地：这里再无可供他们研究之物。夏暮的旗帜在风中孤零地飘扬。","0":"一群学者在林地边缘扎营。他们的资金已经枯竭，但仍试图继续研究那位埋葬于摄政王之墓中的存在。

风在树林中呼啸，乌云密布欲雨。学者们蜷缩在帐篷里，沉思着论文，暗中算计彼此。"}}

