original:
{"Conversation":{"1":"He smiles like a child, who has just seen something magical. "Did you hear how they gasped?" he asks, mimicking the audience with exaggerated features of surprise. His smile widens, and he takes another puff. "It's been a long time since I've heard that."","2":"The Magician distracts himself by performing small coin tricks. In time though, he loses track of which pocket he's sneaked what into, and sighs. 

"It all keeps breaking down," he says. "No matter what we do, it's never enough."","0":""It breaks my heart you had to sit through that," he says, nodding toward the big top. "Sometimes I wonder why I left Mahogany Hall. Then I remember how much Plenty paid, before this whole place lost its funding." 

He puts out the cigarette on the poster, then tosses it into an overturned top-hat.","5":"He's cleared a cushion for you to sit on, atop his famous 'box of certain death'. He rolls up his sleeves, reaches behind your ear, and produces a cigarette. "Smoke?""}}

translation:
{"Conversation":{"1":"他笑得像刚看到神奇事物的孩子。"你听到他们惊愕的吸气声了吗？"他问道，模仿着观众惊讶的夸张表情。他的笑意更浓，又抽了一口烟，"那种声音我已经很久没有听到过了。"","2":"魔术师通过表演小硬币的戏法来打发时间。然而，随着时间的推移，他已经不知道自己把什么东西偷偷放进哪个口袋了，于是叹了口气。

"这一切都在崩溃，"他说，"无论我们做什么，都永远不够。","0":""我对你你不得不坐在那里而感到伤心，"他说，朝大帐篷点了点头，"有时我想知道为什么我离开桃花心木厅。然后我便想起在这整个地方失去赞助之前，普伦蒂付出了多少。"

他掐灭了海报上的香烟，然后把它扔进了一个翻倒的大帽子里。","5":"他为你清理了放在著名的“必死之箱”上的垫子，让你坐在上面。他卷起袖子，把手伸到你的耳后，变出一支烟。"抽烟吗？""}}

original:
{"Conversation":{"2":"The Clown stares at his geese forlornly. "I can't understand them," he says. "They dent crowns, tear up silks. They won't come out unless they're in costume, but they keep destroying them. I'm sorry for their rudeness."","1":"Cuddles and Ruffles are nestled by the Pensive Clown. "They came through the Avid Horizon with me," he says. "I brought them with me from quite a long ways away. Cuddles is from the heartland of England, and Ruffles—" 

The geese honk. He laughs, and spreads his hands. "Well, I guess they don't want me to give away all their mystique."   ","5":"The Clown and his two pet geese, Cuddles and Ruffles, welcome you. The Clown offers you a bit of bread to feed them. "I don't know where I'd be without them. Or what I'd do if something happened to them," he says. 

"I've thought about it quite often. No other act of mine seems to make people so happy. I don't get laughs alone." He smiles, though, when his geese honk.","0":"The Clown rubs the back of his head. "It's troubling to me that the show goes on, even if no one's there to watch it." He looks to you, searchingly. What does he expect you to say?"}}

translation:
{"Conversation":{"2":"小丑忧伤地望着他的鹅。"我搞不懂它们，"他说，"它们会去凿王冠，撕绸缎。它们不穿上演出服就不肯出来，可又总把演出服弄坏。我为它们的无礼感到抱歉。"","1":"忧郁的小丑身旁依偎着抱抱与荷叶边，"他们是和我一起穿越渴求之地平线来的。"他说，"我带着他们从很远的地方来到这里。抱抱来自英格兰腹地，至于荷叶边——" 

鹅叫了起来。他笑了笑，摊开双手。"好吧，看样子它们不想让我揭露太多神秘。"   ","5":"小丑和他的两只宠鹅，抱抱与荷叶边，热情地欢迎你。小丑递给你一小块面包，想让你喂它们。"没有它们，我不知道我会变成什么样。要是它们出事了，我也不知道该怎么办，"他说。

"我常常这样想。我的其他表演都没法让人这么开心。我一个人演出时没人笑。"不过，当鹅叫起来时，他还是笑了。","0":"小丑挠了挠后脑勺。"让我烦恼的是，即使没有观众，演出也还得继续。"他若有所求地望向你。他希望你说些什么？"}}

original:
{"storm_description":{"0":"Here in the eye of the storm, the winds ease. You are ringed by scudding clouds. A pallid radiance illuminates your engine, like the ghost of sunlight.

Purple lightning threads the storm. The voices on the wind clamour, until a grumble of irritable thunder stills them.","1":"Here in the eye of the storm, the winds ease. You are ringed by scudding clouds. A silver radiance illuminates your engine, like resurgent moonlight.

Purple lightning threads the storm. The voices on the wind clamour, until a peal of stern thunder stills them."},"not_satisfied":{"0":"You cast the souls one by one into the storm. The thunder glowers. The voices on the wind babble and quail. The Storm that Speaks is not satisfied.","1":"You cast the souls one by one into the storm. A silvery peal of thunder, almost like derisive laughter. The Storm that Schemes is not satisfied."},"appeased":{"0":"The souls are luminous against the dark winds. The storm is intrigued. It reaches out a jagged finger of lightning. There is a flash, an acrid smell of copper and melted glass. The storm's voices murmur. Your transgression is forgotten.","1":"The souls are luminous against the dark winds. For a moment, the storm-clouds part; a beam of moonlight shines from the depths, catching, ensnaring. There is a flash, an acrid smell of copper and melted glass. The storm's voices murmur. Your transgression is forgiven."},"appeased2":{"0":"One by one, the souls spin, unremarked, into the storm. But the next one you throw catches the storm's attention. It reaches out a jagged finger of lightning. There is a flash, an acrid smell of copper and melted glass. The storm's voices murmur. Your transgression is forgotten.","1":"One by one, the souls spin, unremarked, into the storm. But the next one you throw catches the storm's attention. For a moment, the clouds part; a beam of moonlight shines from the depths, catching, ensnaring. There is a flash, an acrid smell of copper and melted glass. The storm's voices murmur. Your transgression is forgiven."},"storm_name":{"0":"The Storm that Speaks","1":"The Storm that Schemes"},"odd_one":{"0":"Before you can hear a voice from your own history, the storm resounds with thunder. Irritable lightning stabs the sky. It believes the voices have said too much. There is a crawling sense of pressure on your engine, like a summer's day beneath a gathering storm.","1":"Before you can hear a voice from your own history, the storm resounds with thunder. Irritable lightning stabs the sky. For a moment, you forget your place – you are struck by visions of castles, forests plunging into valleys, knights on pale horses. It takes hours of lurching confusion before you remember who you really are."}}

translation:
{"storm_description":{"0":"此处，于风暴眼中，狂风衰弱了。你被疾驰的云层环抱着。 一道惨白的闪光照亮了你的机车，好似日光的鬼魂。

紫色闪电在风暴中穿梭。风中的声音喧嚣着，直到一阵烦躁的雷声使其沉寂下来。","1":"此处，于风暴眼中，狂风衰弱了。你被疾驰的云层环抱着。 一道银白的闪光照亮了你的机车，好似复归的月光。

紫色闪电在风暴中穿梭。风中的声音喧嚣着，直到一阵烦躁的雷声使其沉寂下来。"},"not_satisfied":{"0":"你把灵魂一个接一个地投入风暴。雷声轰鸣。风中的声音咿咿呀呀地叫着。言语之风暴神并不满意。","1":"你把灵魂一个接一个地投入风暴。雷声轰鸣。风中的声音咿咿呀呀地叫着。蓄谋之风暴神并不满意。"},"appeased":{"0":"灵魂发出的光亮透过了晦暗的风。风暴起了兴趣。祂伸出一根锯齿状的闪电手指。一道闪光，一股铜和玻璃融化的刺鼻气味。风暴喃喃自语。你的过错被遗忘了。","1":"灵魂发出的光亮透过了晦暗的风。刹那间，风暴的乌云散开了；一束月光自深处照来，抓住了它，捕获了它。一道闪光，一股铜和玻璃融化的刺鼻气味。风暴喃喃自语。你的过错被遗忘了。"},"appeased2":{"0":"灵魂一个一个地旋转着，无知无觉地被投进风暴中。但你扔出的下一个灵魂引起了风暴的注意。祂伸出一根锯齿状的闪电手指。一道闪光，一股铜和玻璃融化的刺鼻气味。风暴喃喃自语。你的过错被遗忘了。","1":"灵魂一个一个地旋转着，无知无觉地被投进风暴中。但你扔出的下一个灵魂引起了风暴的注意。刹那间，风暴的乌云散开了；一束月光自深处照来，抓住了它，捕获了它。一道闪光，一股铜和玻璃融化的刺鼻气味。风暴喃喃自语。你的过错被遗忘了。"},"storm_name":{"0":"言语之风暴神","1":"蓄谋之风暴神"},"odd_one":{"0":"在听到来自你自己过往的声音之前，风暴中回响起雷鸣。狂躁的闪电刺破天空。祂认为这些声音说得太多了。你的机车感受到一股窜起的压力，就像一个顶着将临风暴的夏日。","1":"在听到来自你自己过往的声音之前，风暴中回响起雷鸣。狂躁的闪电刺破天空。有那么一瞬间，你忘记了自己身处何处，你被城堡、陷入山谷的森林、骑着苍白马匹的骑士的幻觉所震撼。几个小时的头晕目眩之后，你才想起自己到底是谁。"}}

original:
{"Ingoing":{"11":"Two aristocratic young ladies exchange gossip in the queue before the treatment chambers. "And whom do you have him play?" "Father's butler, of course. Back on our estate in Bugsby's?" "Yes, I recall. For myself, mother's lawyer. Though I can always see the attendant's beauty mark under the make-up." "Beauty mark? He doesn't have a beauty mark?" There is a long silence.","21":"An attendant shakes her head as a merchant in a threadbare suit waves at her. She walks away, face set in a slight frown. The trader flushes, aware he has breached the social covenant of Magdalene's. ","31":"An elderly grand dame is haranguing an attendant. "Yes, but where is my husband? That gentleman was most assuredly not he!" Hushed murmuring follows, interrupted by a loud cry, "No, I did not misunderstand the rules. He's joined your staff!" ","41":"A trio of guests is going in together, all dark haired and straight-backed. "Yes I know it's not the real thing, but I'd like a sense of closure," the tall woman says. "What rot!," barks the short woman next to her, "You want to argue over the will again. I have told you once I am not giving up the spoons based on a charlatan's say-so!" "Do be quiet, please", the one man says. "I for one am more than happy to hear again why I was lumbered with the third best wardrobe." ","0":"Skyfarers cluster outside the doors of the inner chambers, waiting impatiently for their appointments.","1":"A skyfarer clutches a basket of chocolates to him. "I hope it's all right. They don't normally allow this sort of thing, but he is my own father." He coughs, mindful of the Amenable Host's pointed stare, "In a fashion.""},"Outgoing":{"51":"A set of attendants guide a frail old woman out from the chamber doors. Tears line her wrinkled face. "So nice to see everybody again, for the first time since the Tomb-Colonies!" She rummages in her bag and produces a set of figs. "Take these for Gladys. I know I shouldn't, but last time I heard her belly rumbling something rotten. Almost spoiled the scene!" ","61":"A poet staggers through the doors, clutching a sack of wine. An attendant steadies him, while eyeing her colleague meaningfully. A mark is added to a name on a record book.","71":"A harassed captain waits by the steps for his crew to emerge one by one from the chambers below. Each he grabs by the ear and leads to a quiet antechamber. The shouting can be heard from here. "If you had complaints about my captaining, you could have just told me directly! Not some ruddy actor!" ","81":"A priest wanders past, humming a decidedly secular song. He rubs his hands with glee. "My god," he says to nobody in particular, "this is much better than confession."","91":"Seven devils emerge from the chambers, their eyes all alight. They huddle in the atrium, apparently comparing notes.","0":"Some leave smiling, others weeping. No one can resist looking back behind them, even for just a peek."},"Assisting":{"1":"The attendant sighs as you go over her lines together. "I don't even know what a baronet is." She frowns. "Some kind of root vegetable?"","11":"The face powder the attendant is using is cloying. He flexes his shoulders, cracking each knuckle in his hands. "The pay was worse in the Parlour but the work easier. I don't know how many more long-lost sons I've got in me."","31":"Two attendants ask you to juggle with them. "I think our client was one of three. Gotta keep the movements precise; now move your wrist a bit. No! Ah, yes. Like that!" They take deep breaths and face each other like a harlequin before a mirror. "Ready?"","41":"The attendant finishes applying the brush to her wig. "I don't suppose you're familiar with Her Majesty personally? No?" She quirks an eyebrow in her mirror. "Ah well. I don't suppose tonight's client is either. How amusing."","21":""'And let me not be wrong about you.'" The attendant frowns as she finishes her line reading. "But she was. He never came back for her." She bunches her hand into a fist before shaking it out. "And now I get to go and play the salve for his guilt."","0":"The backrooms are a bustle of activity; frenetic and frantic, everyone powdering their faces or adjusting costumes in time for the first shift of the day."},"Drinks":{"51":"An attendant dressed as Ellen Terry shares a brandy with you by the great fireplace. The flickering firelight gleams in the surrounding stained glass. She raises her glass in a toast. "To all we could be."","81":"A beautiful attendant provides you with as much sherry as you could ever ask for. It soon becomes apparent they are looking for as much information on skyfaring as they're able. You give as much as time and sherry allow.","91":"You watch attendants drift in and out of the room, bearing glasses, costumes, props, bottles, and postures. Some come to speak with you, others watch, noting your bearing, your habits, your mannerisms. No doubt some of you will remain here, repeated, in these stained glass chambers of the heart.","71":"Chequers and whiskey are the order of the day. A tournament is organised. Good whiskey for wins, bad for forfeits, extra shifts for losses, excepting yourself, of course. Your penalty is to do the washing up. The afternoon passes in a pleasant haze.","0":"Glasses gleam in mellow candlelight. A party is being prepared. No customers allowed.","61":"You share a bottle of Wilderness-chilled wine with a troupe of attendants, fresh from a circus performance. "They expect us to keep up with Polmear and Plenty's!" one tired amateur acrobat complains. 

"Should we ask our Host for an instructor?" an exhausted Strongwoman asks. 

A grey-faced magician shakes his head. "This job. Do we need to have experienced everything to be anyone?""}}

translation:
{"Ingoing":{"11":"两个年轻的贵族小姐在治疗间外的队伍中窃窃私语。"你让他扮演谁？" "当然是父亲的管家。你还记得我们在巴格斯比那儿的庄园里那个吗？" "我记得。我的话，是母亲的律师。虽然我总能从妆容下看到侍者的那颗美人痣。" "美人痣？他没有美人痣吧？" 接下来是一阵长久的沉默。","21":"一个身穿破旧西装的商人朝一位侍者挥手，她摇了摇头离开，脸上带着轻微的不悦。那位商人脸红了，意识到自己违反了抹大拉之家的社交契约。","31":"一位年迈的贵妇正在训斥一位侍者。"是的，可我丈夫在哪儿？刚才那位绅士可绝对不是他！"低声的议论随之而来，被一声大喊打断："不，我没有误解规定。他是你们这儿的员工！" ","41":"三位客人一同走进内室，三人皆黑发笔直。"我知道这不是真的，但我希望有个了结。"高个女人说道。"胡说八道！"旁边矮个女人吼道，"你就是想再争遗嘱。我已经说了，我不会因为一个骗子的话就把那套餐匙让给你！" "安静点，好吗。"那唯一的男士说，"我倒是很乐意再听听为何我只能得到第三好的衣柜。" ","0":"行天客们聚集在内室门外，焦急等待着他们的预约。","1":"一位行天客紧紧抱着一篮子巧克力。"我希望这样没问题。他们通常不允许带这种东西，但那可是我父亲。"他轻咳一声，注意到随和主管犀利的目光，"某种意义上的父亲。""},"Outgoing":{"51":"几位侍者搀扶着一位虚弱的老妇人走出内室。她布满皱纹的脸上挂着泪水。"真高兴又能见到大家，自从古墓殖民地之后我就再没见过了！"她在包里翻找，掏出一包无花果。"拿去给格莱迪斯。我知道我不该带，可上次听到她肚子饿得咕咕叫，差点毁了场景！" ","61":"一位诗人踉跄着从门后走出，手中紧抓一袋酒。一位侍者扶住他，同时意味深长地看了她的同事一眼。记录本上的名字旁被加上了一笔记号。","71":"一位疲惫的车长在台阶旁等待列车员们一个个从下方的房间走出来。他把每个人揪住耳朵，拉到一间安静的前室。他的吼声在这里都能听得到："你们对我的车长指挥有意见，大可以直接告诉我！别找个破演员！" ","81":"一位牧师哼着一首明显世俗的歌走过。他搓着手，面露喜色。"我的上帝啊，"他自言自语道，"这比忏悔可带劲多了。"","91":"七位恶魔从房间里走出来，眼中燃着光。他们聚在中庭，似乎正在交换笔记。","0":"有些人笑着离开，有些人泪流满面。人人皆回头而视，哪怕只有一瞥。"},"Assisting":{"1":"你和侍者一起反复排练台词，她叹了口气。"我甚至不知道男爵是什么。"她皱着眉，"某种根茎类蔬菜？"","11":"侍者正使用的面粉香味扑鼻。他活动肩膀，指节一一作响。"在沙龙那边薪水更少，但工作也轻松些。我不知道我还能扮演多少个失散多年的儿子。"","31":"两个侍者请你和他们一起练杂耍。"我想我们的客户是杂耍三人组中的一人。动作得精准点。来，动动手腕。不是那样——啊，对，就那样！"他们深吸一口气，彼此对视，如镜前小丑。"准备好了吗？"","41":"侍者给她的假发上完妆。"你不会恰好认识女王陛下吧？不认识？"她对着镜子扬了扬眉。"嗯，那今晚的客人八成也不认识。真不错。"","21":""'愿我对你没有看错。'"侍者皱眉念完台词，"可她确实看错了。他再也没回来。"她握拳又松开。"而我现在得去当他的赎罪剂。"","0":"后台一片忙乱，所有人都在为第一班轮换做准备，纷纷扑粉、整理服装，场面热烈又混乱。"},"Drinks":{"51":"一位装扮成艾伦·特里的侍者在大壁炉旁与你共饮白兰地。火光在四周彩绘玻璃上闪烁。她举杯致意："敬我们可能成为的一切。"","81":"一位美丽的侍者源源不断地为你提供雪利酒。不久你就发现，此人想尽量从你这儿打听有关行天的一切。你尽量在雪利酒允许的时间内倾诉了所知所感。","91":"你看着侍者们进进出出，有的拿着酒杯、服装、道具、瓶子，或带着各种表情。他们中有的来和你交谈，有的则默默观察，记录你的姿态、习惯、举止。毫无疑问，你的一部分将留在这里，在这座心灵的彩色玻璃殿堂中，反复上演。","71":"今天的主题是跳棋和威士忌。一场锦标赛随之展开。胜者喝好酒，弃权者喝劣酒，输者加班——当然，你除外。你的惩罚是去洗碗。一个慵懒的下午在酒意朦胧中悄然溜走。","0":"在柔和的烛光下，酒杯熠熠生辉。一场派对正在筹备之中。顾客止步。","61":"你与一群刚表演完马戏的侍者共饮一瓶野地冰镇酒。"他们居然希望我们能和波尔梅尔和普伦蒂的马戏团比肩！"一位疲惫的业余杂技演员抱怨道。

"我们该请主管给我们找个教练吗？"一位筋疲力尽的女大力士问。

一位面色灰白的魔术师摇了摇头。"真是苦差事。我们真的得经历一切，才能成为任何人吗？""}}

original:
{"Parzifal":{"0":"Parzifal","1":"Spores drift through broken carriages like dying fireflies. Recruitment posters bearing Her Renewed Majesty's face moulder on the walls. Music, scratchy but distinct, echoes through the empty carriages. A great wall of pulsing fungus separates the back of the engine from the front.
","5":"The front of the engine is even more infected with sprouting mushrooms and sporing fungal growths. The engine room lies ahead, seemingly the source of the persistent movement. Before that, however, is a haze of spores rendering the corridor ahead entirely noxious.","10":"The engine room is before you. Light and music spill from under the door, queasy and persistent."},"Percy":{"0":"Percy","30":"The engine room is cold as a sunless sky. Your breath hangs in long chains before you. The boiler is off. The infernal gramophone sits atop the boiler. The music is no better for being closer to it.

Before you lies a danse macabre of fungus and corpses, hand in frond. On the wall, suspended by fungus, is a body in a captain's uniform. ","40":"Suspended from chains of fungus, Percy Blythe begins to stir, improbably alive. He fixes his gold-flecked eyes on you, as his mouth begins to move as though wanting to speak.","60":"Blythe hangs listless in front of you, apparently exhausted. His head lolls and his gaze is dull. What is to be done?","50":"The Lt Commander of the Parzifal has survived whatever befell his engine. He is the key to understanding whatever occurred here."}}

translation:
{"Parzifal":{"0":"帕西法尔","1":"孢子像垂死的萤火虫一样飘过破碎的车厢。印有新生的女王陛下面孔的招募海报在墙上发霉。沙哑但可辨的音乐在空荡荡的车厢中回荡。一堵巨大的搏动真菌墙将发动机的后部和前部阻隔开。
","5":"机车前部被发芽的蘑菇和孢子状的真菌感染得更为严重。引擎室在前面，似乎是持续运动的源头。然而，在到达那里之前，一片孢子的阴霾使前面的走廊变得毒气充溢。","10":"引擎室就在你面前。光线和音乐从门下溢出，令人恶心，久久不止。"},"Percy":{"0":"帕西","30":"引擎室寒冷如无光之空。你呼出的雾气向上吊起，有如长链。锅炉已经停转。糟糕的留声机就放在在锅炉的顶部。音乐并没有因为离它更近而变得更悦耳。

你面前是一片由真菌和尸体组成的恐怖之舞，他们的手和叶状体连接在一起。在墙上，一具穿着车长制服的尸体挂在真菌上。","40":"悬在真菌链条上的珀西·布莱斯开始扭动。难以置信地，他还活着。他把他那双泛着金光的眼睛盯着你，他的嘴开始移动，似乎想要说话。","60":"布莱斯萎靡地挂在你面前，显然已耗尽力气。他的头耷拉着，目光呆滞。该怎么做？","50":"帕西法尔号的上尉从他的机车的遭遇中幸存。他是了解这里发生的一切的关键。"}}

original:
{"Root":{"10":"Her interior is cold, unlit and whistles with wind. Your party's lamps spread buttery light over the narrow, panelled passages. You make your way towards the hold, stepping over bodies crumpled in the corridor. 

Unfortunately, your way is blocked. A bulkhead has been mangled inward by a well-aimed barrage.","20":"You have reached the <i>Ozymandias</i>' hold: a ruin of smashed cargo and spilled supplies. Hopefully, somewhere amidst the detritus, you can find parts to repair the Orphean and restock your stores.","25":"The <i>Ozymandias</i> emits a long, juddering creak. Your boarding party exchange nervous glances.

From the chaos of its hold you have retrieved repairs and supplies, and discovered some useful equipment: a gun that could be mounted on your locomotive, and an educated bat.","0":"The wreck hangs in the sky, pocked with recent gunfire. You and the boarding party don your sky-suits: garments of waxed canvas, lined with felt to protect against the cold of the sky. Two of the crew are whispering as they dress. "What business did Captain Whitlock have in the Blue Kingdom anyway? Why the devil did we trespass on the districts of the dead?" You silence him. Now's not the time."}}

translation:
{"Root":{"10":"舱内一片漆黑，寒风呼啸。你们点起灯笼，金黄的光芒洒在狭窄的镶板走廊上。你们朝货舱进发，途中跨过一具具倒毙在过道上的尸体。

不幸的是，去路被堵住了。一发精准的炮击将一处舱壁严重扭曲，向内塌陷。","20":"你们已抵达<i>奥兹曼迪亚斯号</i>的货舱：一片被打碎的货物与撒落的补给构成的废墟。希望在这片残骸中，你们能找到足以修理俄耳甫斯号，并补充储备的零件。","25":"<i>奥兹曼迪亚斯号</i>发出一声悠长而颤抖的呻吟。你们的探索队员彼此交换了不安的眼神。

你们从凌乱的货舱中找到了修理材料与补给，还发现了一些有用的装备：一门可以安装到你机车上的火炮，以及一只受过训练的蝙蝠。","0":"这艘残骸悬挂在空中，遍布着新近的弹痕。你和探索队员穿上了潜天装：这种服装以打蜡帆布制成，内衬毡布，以抵御天野的寒冷。两名列车员一边穿戴一边低声私语："惠特洛克车长当初为何要去蓝色王国？我们又为何要闯入亡者的辖域？"你止住了他。现在不是说这个的时候。"}}
